<br>
Imagine my surprise when he agreed :-)<br>
<br>
So, I led him over the bloodgills and let him drown himself.  Was chuckling for a bit, waiting for the moron to get back to the spot so that I could pay him his 100p and watch him CR when I got a tell out of the blue from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>another</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> druid saying that he would drown himself for 50p.  He proceeded to find me, came out over the Lake and drowned himself, /bog.<br>
<br>
Well, apparently the rumors spread like wildfire... because soon I had 6 people busy killing themselves over the bloodgills for 20-50p each.  I actually had to go to FV to get more cash.<br>
<br>
Did I mention that the bloodgills weren't being camped?  They'd come running up from FV (or wherever they were bound), dive in, get blindsided, die, and do it all over again.  Pretty soon, there must have been 50 corpses down there.<br>
<br>
Finally, I went down and held the spawn of bloodgills so that they could retrieve their corpses.  Of course, a number of them were unclear on the concept of breathing, so they would loot 1, 2, maybe 3 corpses and then die again.  So, I started passing out waterstones, but even with those a number of them drowned.<br>
<br>
Gods, it was funny.  I burned 3kp paying druids to drown themselves. :-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=steeleyelandsaver>Steeleye Landsaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 7:25:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=252.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I must have been in a mood...</span><hr size=1> LOL....good money for a GOOD cause.  Silly Druids<br>
